      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISTER DEVEREAUX (6) has finished runner-up in both starts so far this campaign, turning in a strong performance last time when he battled on bravely to miss out by 1.2m at Melton. Draws wider but should be close to his peak now and is suited returning to maiden grade so is a strong winning hope. RIPPING RONALDO (8) was well in the betting when making his first appearance but manners let him down. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and has shown enough at the trials to suggest he has ability so he is worth another chance. DALAHASTEN (1) did a good job last time out, coming from the back row to finish second at Maryborough. Can be competitive from the ace draw. PARDRAY (5) locked wheels when resuming so could do better.",
